---

## 3. TYPESCRIPT

- **No `any`** — use `unknown` with type guards instead.
- **No `React.FC`** — use explicit prop interfaces and return types.
- Use `interface` for component props and object shapes; `type` for unions, aliases, and utility types.
- Avoid deprecated React event types (e.g. `React.FormEvent`). Prefer handler types (`React.FormEventHandler<HTMLFormElement>`) or minimal structural types (`{ preventDefault: () => void }`).
- Never suppress errors with `@ts-ignore`; fix the type or use a narrower cast with a comment explaining why.
- All Server Actions must return a structured result: `{ success: boolean; data?: T; error?: string }`.

---

## 4. NEXT.JS 16 — RENDERING & DATA

- **Server-first**: Default to Server Components. Add `'use client'` only when the component uses browser APIs, React hooks, or event handlers.
- **Params/SearchParams**: In Next.js 16 App Router, `params` and `searchParams` are Promises — always `await` them in Pages and Layouts.
- **Data fetching**: Use native `fetch` with Next.js caching options for reads. Use Server Actions for all writes and mutations.
- **Forms**: Use `useActionState` (React 19) + `useFormStatus` for form state and pending UI. Do not use deprecated `useFormState`.
- **Error handling**: Add `error.tsx` boundaries per route segment.
- **Metadata**: Export `metadata` objects or `generateMetadata()` from Server Components.
- There is **no** `use cache` directive in Next.js 16 — do not generate it. Use `fetch` cache options and `revalidateTag` / `revalidatePath`.

---

## 5. TAILWIND CSS 4

- **No `tailwind.config.js`** — this project uses CSS-first configuration exclusively.
- All theme tokens are defined in `app/globals.css` under `@theme inline` and `:root`.
- Always use the semantic tokens defined in the project — never hardcode hex values in `className`:

| Token                    | Value              | Usage                         |
| ------------------------ | ------------------ | ----------------------------- |
| `bg-background`          | `#FDF8F3` Ivory    | Main page canvas              |
| `text-foreground`        | `#1C1C1C` Charcoal | Primary text                  |
| `bg-muted`               | `#F5EFE9` Beige    | Inactive tabs, subtle fills   |
| `text-muted-foreground`  | `#6B6B6B` Gray     | Secondary / placeholder text  |
| `bg-card`                | `#FFFFFF` White    | Card surfaces                 |
| `border-border`          | `#E8E0D7` Stone    | All borders                   |
| `text-accent` / `bg-accent` | `#A47864` Mocha | Highlights, icons, focus ring |
| `bg-primary`             | `#1C1C1C` Black    | Primary buttons               |
| `bg-secondary`           | `#E8E0D7`          | Right-panel editorial column  |
| `text-destructive`       | `#dc2626` Red      | Errors and destructive actions|

- Use `cn()` (from `@/lib/utils` — `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) for all conditional className composition.
- Font variables: `--font-sans` (Inter), `--font-mono` (JetBrains Mono), `--font-serif` (Playfair Display, used in quote carousels and editorial text).
- Border radius: `--radius` = `0.5rem` base; use `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl` from the scale.

---

## 6. CLERK v7 AUTH

- **Provider**: `ClerkProvider` wraps the root layout in `app/layout.tsx`.
- **Custom sign-in UI**: Use `useSignIn()` hook — do NOT render the prebuilt `<SignIn />` component. The custom form lives in `components/auth/custom-sign-in-form.tsx`.
- **Password sign-in**: `signIn.password({ emailAddress, password })` → check `signIn.status` → `signIn.finalize({ navigate })`.
- **OAuth (Google, Apple)**: `signIn.sso({ strategy, redirectCallbackUrl: '/sso-callback', redirectUrl })`. The SSO callback is handled in `app/sso-callback/page.tsx`.
- **Social buttons**: Reusable component at `components/auth/social-auth-buttons.tsx`; accepts `onSignInWith(strategy: OAuthStrategy)` callback.
- **Login types**: Personal and Institution tabs exist for UX only (same Clerk strategy). Store `loginType` in Clerk `publicMetadata` when differentiating later.
- **Clerk × Supabase**: Access Supabase via the Clerk JWT using `auth.getToken({ template: 'supabase' })` to enforce Row Level Security (RLS).
- **Middleware**: Use `clerkMiddleware()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server` for route protection.
- **Webhooks**: Use Clerk Webhooks with `svix` to sync user data to Supabase `profiles`. Verify using `CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET` from `.env.local`.
- **RBAC**: Use Clerk `publicMetadata` for role-based access control to avoid extra DB queries.
- **Required env vars** (all in `.env.local`):
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`
  - `CLERK_SECRET_KEY`
  - `CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in`

---

## 7. PROJECT STRUCTURE

```
app/
  layout.tsx                   — Root layout with ClerkProvider, fonts
  globals.css                  — Tailwind 4 theme + CSS variables
  page.tsx                     — Landing / Supabase demo
  about/page.tsx
  admin/page.tsx                — Admin dashboard (School Admin / System Admin toggle)
  admin/layout.tsx
  profile/page.tsx             — User profile (protected)
  profile/layout.tsx
  sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/page.tsx  — Custom sign-in (uses CustomSignInForm)
  sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/page.tsx  — Clerk SignUp with AuthLayout
  sso-callback/page.tsx        — OAuth redirect handler

components/
  auth/
    custom-sign-in-form.tsx    — Custom Personal/Institution sign-in form
    social-auth-buttons.tsx    — Reusable Google/Apple OAuth buttons
  auth-layout.tsx              — Two-column auth shell (form left, quote carousel right)
  admin/                       — Admin dashboard widgets
  profile/                     — Profile page sections and panels
  header.tsx / footer.tsx / hero.tsx / features.tsx / pricing.tsx / cta.tsx

lib/
  utils.ts                     — cn() utility
```

- Follow this existing structure. Do not invent new top-level directories.
- Place auth-related components in `components/auth/`.
- Place route-specific server components in their `app/` route folder.
- Place shared UI components in `components/`.

---

## 8. COMPONENT PATTERNS

- Input fields: `h-11`, `rounded-md`, `border border-border`, `bg-card`, `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring`.
- Primary buttons: `h-11 w-full rounded-md border border-primary bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90`.
- Tabs (Personal/Institution): `rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted p-1` container; active tab: `bg-card text-foreground shadow-sm`.
- Icons: Always use `lucide-react`. Match icon `strokeWidth` to context (nav icons typically `1.5`–`1.6`).
- Charts (`recharts`): Always wrap in a `'use client'` component.
- Avoid inline styles except for animation values (e.g. `opacity`, `transform` for carousels).

---

## 9. AI INTERACTION PROTOCOL

- Skip explanations of stable, well-known APIs. Focus on non-obvious logic and trade-offs.
- For changes spanning multiple files, always present a **Step-by-Step Implementation Plan** before writing code.
- Reference `@package.json` for exact versions and `@.env.local` for env variables.
- After substantive edits, check for linter errors using the `ReadLints` tool and fix any introduced issues.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly asked.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Never use `echo` or shell commands to communicate — output all explanations as response text.
